# Rails Conventions

## Structure

- Follow Rails 8 conventions (Omakase-style via rubocop-rails-omakase)
- Use standard MVC; keep models thin, logic in services where appropriate
- Financial logic belongs in services, not controllers or models

## Naming

- Models: singular (PostingBatch, AccountTransaction)
- Tables: plural snake_case (posting_batches, account_transactions)
- Services: `*Service` suffix (e.g. PostingService, ReversalService)

## Financial Code

- Never put posting logic in controllers; use a service object
- Wrap posting commits in `ActiveRecord::Base.transaction`
- Use `raise ActiveRecord::Rollback` on validation failure, not `return`
